LongDescription:
One of the naval offices newest additions, the Pskellon class corvette has been in use with the Falcatan navy for less than a decade. The class was designed primarily to fill the roll of point defense and sensor escort, something that the naval asset pool had been sorely lacking for the better part of its history. 

While a lone Pskellon might struggle, these ships thrive as escorts or in groups, where their weaker firepower is negated, and their combination of utility and solid maneuverability can be exercized to its greatest extent.

Identification Work Required: +125%
